psmRevdesc:
Hi, I'm Neha Nagpal, and you're watching Project Review on MBTV. Today I'm in Attapur which is located in the southwest part of Hyderabad. I am going to review a project launched by Mahaveer Constructions. It is called the Crystal Garden. Stay tuned with me as I review the project based on its location, price, builder profile, specification and much more.

Mahaveer Construction is a Bengaluru based company which started operations in 1998. They have delivered 115 real estate projects which are a mix of residential and commercial. They started their Hyderabad operations in 2019. Apart from the Crystal Garden, the developer has three ongoing projects in the city at different stages of construction.

Let's check out the project now.

Spread across five acres, the Crystal Garden is a gated community that's been constructed using MIVAN technology. Currently the excavation work is underway and the project is likely to be ready for the possession by March 2026.

The project will have three towers of G + 35 floors each with four level basement parking. There are a total of 782 apartments in three and four bedroom configurations in varied sizes. The size of 3 BHKs starts from 1600 sq ft and goes up to 2360 sq ft. For 4 BHKs there are two size options that are 4550 sq ft. and 4706 sq ft. The smaller size in 4 BHK is only available on the ground floor. In tower one, there will be four units of 4 BHK plus servant room on each floor while towers two and three will have nine 3 BHK units on each floor.

The price of apartments in the Crystal Garden starts from rupees 1 crore 16 lakh and goes up to three crore 50 lakhs. Stamp duty, registration charges, legal documentation and society maintenance deposit will be charged extra. The developer will maintain the property for two years after possession and will charge Rs 4 per sq ft in advance for two years at the time of registration.

The Crystal garden is situated in Attapur below PVNR Expressway. The approach road to the project is well laid. Employment hubs of hitec City, Gachibowli and Financial district are 11 to18 km and 20 to 30 minutes away via Inner Ring Road and Old Mumbai Highway.

Lakdi ka Pul Metro station which is about 6 km from the project is the nearest and will take you approximately 15 minutes to reach. Nampally Railway Station is about 9 km and 25 minutes away from the project while Secunderabad Railway Station is about 16 km from here. Rajiv Gandhi International Airport is at a distance of 23km usually takes you about 30 minutes to reach via PVNR Expressway. Finding autos, cabs and buses is quite convenient too.

The social infrastructure around the project is well developed. Begum Bazaar, the commercial hub of the city is about 6 km from the project. From food, grocery, clothing, accessories you will find everything in this market.

The famous tourist place Charminar is about 9 km from here.

Since Attapur enjoys good accessibility to major employment hubs in the city, many IT professionals are looking to invest in this locality. For grocery shopping, Ratnadeep Supermarket is only 100 meters away. There are many local shops as well to cater to your daily needs. From restaurants, salons, Andes, pharmacies and vegetable markets, everything is at a walkable distance from the project.

Solitaire Global School and St Ann’s College are educational institutions close to the project. Additionally, Chaitanya Junior College, Gokaraju Rangaraju College of Engineering and JNTU are located within a five kilometer radius. Hospitals like Germanten, Maitreyi and Olive are within 3 km of the project. Mantra Mall is about 5 km away.

Other than the Crystal Garden, there are no ongoing projects in the immediate vicinity. However, Kenworth by Providence Developers and Aparna One by Aparna Constructions are within 7 km from the project Kenworth by Providence offer property at the rate of Rs 7000 per square feet apart. Aparna one by Aparna Construction is available at the rate of Rs 12,000 per square feet, while the Crystal Garden offers property at the rate of Rs 7500 per square feet.

According to Magicbricks data, the properties in Attapur are available in the average range of Rs 3800 to 6100 per square feet. The developer claims that they are providing bigger apartments and huge open space within the premises compared to the other projects in the area at competitive rates.

Talking about the project's investment potential, a semi furnished 3 BHK apartment in the Crystal Garden can fetch your monthly rentals of  Rs 40,000.

In terms of amenities, there will be a clubhouse of 65000 sq ft with a temperature controlled swimming pool, gym, supermarket, pharmacy, clinic, ATMs, restaurants, creche, library, private theater for 32 people, boardrooms and meeting rooms, workstations among others. Guest rooms facility will also be provided in the clubhouse. There will also be a tennis court, half basketball court, jogging and cycling track, cricket pitch and play area for kids 

Attapur does not face any issues with water and electricity supply. Additionally, the developer also has made provisions for a tubewell. The approach road to the project is well laid and has functioning street lights. Attapur Police Station is also nearby. Thus, in terms of safety and security, the project scores quite well. However, you will find severe traffic congestion during peak hours on the road outside the project. 

Attapur is one of Hyderabad's fastest growing areas in terms of real estate. The state circle value has also increased which has driven up property values here. All of these things combine to make Attapur an attractive investment location. Social infrastructure and transportation facilities are in place here.

So if you're looking for a premium home in an established area of Hyderabadad and have a large budget, the Crystal Garden by Mahaveer Construction can be considered.

I hope you like this project review. If you have any, query right to me in the comments section below this video.

To watch more such project reviews, please subscribe MBTV don't forget to like and share this video 

With cameraman Manish Sharma, this is Neha Nagpal  for signing off from Hyderabad.

psmRevdesc:
Hi. I'm Neha Nagpal and you're watching Project Review on MBTV. In this episode I will review a newly launched project Callisto in Hyderabad. This project is by GHR Infra Developers and is situated in Kollur in Tellapur. Stay tuned as I review this project based on its location, price, builder profile, specification and much more.

GHR Infra Developers Ltd is a Hyderabad based real estate company that started operations in 2019. Earlier, the company operated under the name of Gautami Developers which was later changed to GHR which stands for Genuine, Honest and Reliable. Currently, the developer has two ongoing projects in the city namely GHR Titania in Kondapur and Gautami Countryside in Mokila.

Let's head towards the project site now.

Callisto is spread across approximately 8.3 acres. As you can see, the excavation work is going on. The project is slated to be delivered by June 2025.

Callisto will have four towers that will be constructed in two phases. In the first phase, towers one and four will be built while the remaining two towers will be a part of the second phase. there will be a total of 1190 apartments in 2, 3 and 4 BHK configurations.

In the first phase, 646 units will be delivered. Talking about the sizes 2 BHKs- 1195 sq ft and 1295 sq ft, 3 BHKs are available in four sizes 1430 sq ft, 1625 sq ft, 1775 sq ft and 1915 sq ft. Lastly, 4 BHKs in this project are in two sizes 3300 sq ft and 3585 sq ft. Each tower will be stilt + 18 floors with two level basement car parking. The monthly maintenance charges would be Rs 3 per square feet. Towers one, two and four will have 19 units on each floor while tower three will have 13 units on every floor.

The price of apartments in Callisto starts from Rs 57.30 lakh and goes up to Rs 95 lakhs depending on the size and configuration. Please note that the parking charges, stamp duty, registration charges and society maintenance deposit will be extra. 

A 2 BHK of size 1195 sq ft is available in east facing and west facing.  The layout of the east facing will be like this. The door of the apartment opens into a drawing and dining room, to which the kitchen is right adjacent to it. Along with the kitchen you will get a utility space as well. In this apartment you'll get two bedrooms and two toilets. While in the master bedroom a toilet is attached whereas there is one common toilet given right opposite to the dining area which can be accessed from every part of the apartment. The apartment will also have one balcony where you can easily keep two chairs to sit outside 

Callisto is approachable from two roads- from the Outer Ring Road or ORR and from Kokapet Shankarpally Road. From Gachibowli the project is about 18 km and takes about approximately 30 minutes to reach via ORR and exiting at Kokapet exit one The project is about 2 km from Kollur Village. From ORR exit One and Two, one has to pass through the village to reach the project.

While all main roads are well maintained, internal and approach roads require maintenance. Looking at the connectivity with the Railway Station and the airport, Secunderabad Railway Station is about 40 km and one hour ten minutes away from the project, while Rajiv Gandhi International Airport is approximately 41 km and 45 minutes away via ORR.

Since Kollur is an upcoming area, the social infrastructure is also in the nascent stages of development. Samashti International School is the nearest school at a distance of about 3 km. Delhi Public School is also there, which is at a distance of ten minutes drive from the project. However, one has to travel at least 10 to 15 km for good hospitals. Citizens hospitals in Nallagandla and Continental hospitals in the Financial District are easily accessible from the project thanks to swift connectivity via ORR. Kokapet SEZ is about 12 km from Callisto. Once it's functional, it will also positively impact the housing demand in Kollur. The IT hubs of Hitec City and Gachibowli are at a distance of 18 to 25 km from the project.

For daily needs, pharmacy requirements and grocery shopping, there are a few small shops in Kollur Village. However, for leisure and entertainment, one has to travel to Hitec City. Shopping complexes and restaurants along Kokapet Crossroad are also accessible in 20 to 25 minutes.

Kollur is witnessing significant real estate development. There are many ongoing projects within a five km radius of Callisto. IRA Aspiration, Signature LTS, Anvita Sky Garden and EVK Avasa are few to be named. All these projects are slated for possession between 2024 to 2025. Additionally, Dignity Homes by Telangana Government is also 2 km from Callisto. In terms of property rates, these projects are currently demanding anywhere between Rs. 5000 to 5500 per square feet.

As for Magicbricks data, property price in Kollur is available in the range of Rs 2500 to 4500 per square feet.

Moving on to amenities, Callisto will have EV fast charging stations, Smart Home Automation, Reflexology Walkway, Mini golf course, courtyard concept, solar power and water efficient fixtures. Kollur falls under the purview of Tellapur Municipal Corporation and TSSPDCL supplies electricity in the area.

While there are no issues with power supply, water supply is definitely a concern. Currently, you will only find groundwater facilities here. The developer also has made provisions for tubewells and storage tankers within the premises. While main roads are in good condition and well lit during nights, the internal roads require more street lights and more maintenance.
